Hi [~asuresh]

One question, if user specifies several processors in the chain by property {{yarn.resourcemanager.application-master-service.processors}}, e.g P1, P2, P3. The actual chain seems to be defined as

{noformat}
P1 -> P2 -> P3 -> DefaultAMSProcessor
{noformat}

Why {{DefaultAMSProcessor}} should be the last one in the chain? With the context of opportunistic containers, isn't it making more sense to re-order to

{noformat}
DefaultAMSProcessor -> P1 -> P2 -> P3
{noformat}

so that guaranteed containers always get allocated first?

Thanks

